This paper deals with epistemic logics, which are typically studied in the subfield of logic (cs.LO). However, the paper also discusses multi-agent systems and coordination, which are topics commonly studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also uses Kripke-style semantics, which is a common tool in programming languages and semantics (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the coordinated attack problem, which is a problem in distributed computing and communication (cs.CC).
